EIGHT people died when two sedans collided on the R40 between Dwarloop and Violetbank in Bushbuckridge. The crash happened on Saturday evening around 9pm. According to the Department of Community Safety, Jaws of Life had to be used to remove the bodies of the seven who died on the scene. Spokesman for the department Moeti Mmusi said one person was critically injured and died on the way to hospital. He said each vehicle had four occupants, including the drivers. Mmusi said the cause of the crash is yet to be established and the investigations are under way.